&lt;p&gt;Duetto&#39;s legal function is a strategic asset — and this role owns all of it. As VP, Legal, you&#39;ll serve as a key partner to the CFO, Board, and PE sponsor, building the legal infrastructure that supports the company&#39;s growth and exit readiness. This isn&#39;t a compliance seat. It&#39;s a builder role for someone who treats legal as a high-leverage operating system: scalable, increasingly automated, and held to diligence-ready standards from day one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes Us Different?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duetto is the hospitality industry&#39;s leading revenue management platform, founded in 2012 by former Wynn Resorts executives who knew the industry needed better technology. We built the world&#39;s first Revenue &amp;amp; Profit Operating System — a suite of tools (GameChanger, ScoreBoard, BlockBuster, Advance and more) that goes beyond room pricing to give hotels, resorts and casinos a complete picture of their revenue and profitability. Trusted by clients ranging from independent boutique hotels to global chains, we&#39;ve been named the #1 Revenue Management Software by HotelTechAwards four years running and the #1 Best Place to Work in Hotel Tech in 2025. Backed by GrowthCurve Capital since 2024, we&#39;re accelerating our investment in AI — and we&#39;re genuinely passionate about the industry we serve. We build products we&#39;re proud of, for customers we care about.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own&lt;/strong&gt; the legal AI stack — select, implement, and champion AI-powered tooling for contract review, CLM, policy drafting, and regulatory monitoring, and set the standard for how a modern, lean legal function operates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner&lt;/strong&gt; with Product and Engineering on our ML pricing models, developing and maintaining the legal and ethical framework governing data usage, algorithmic decision-making, and pricing transparency, and becoming an expert on hospitality-related compliance trends to influence our product roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive&lt;/strong&gt; high-velocity global growth by architecting scalable commercial contracting processes and playbooks that empower Sales to close deals efficiently while simplifying processes, reducing exceptions, and maintaining necessary protections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build&lt;/strong&gt; exit-readiness into everything we do — operate with a PE mindset, hold our work to diligence-ready standards, and serve as a core member of the corporate functions leadership group, ensuring Legal is deeply integrated with Corp Dev, FP&amp;amp;A, Accounting, and IT to drive cross-functional initiatives, including M&amp;amp;A.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establish&lt;/strong&gt; and refine corporate governance frameworks by serving as Secretary to the Board of Directors, acting as a proactive steward of corporate hygiene, preparing Board-facing materials, and advising on external governance and compliance trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oversee&lt;/strong&gt; the legal budget and external legal relationships at the company and PE-ownership level, allocating resources across internal/external, specialist/generalist, and high/low cost with a bias toward insourcing through technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage&lt;/strong&gt; employment law across a global workforce, partnering with People Operations on complex employment matters, equity agreements, compensation plan structures, and international workforce compliance across all jurisdictions in which the company operates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evolve&lt;/strong&gt; the enterprise risk management function by collaborating with Finance on insurance, tax exposure, and operational risk, with a focus on what materially affects exit valuation.&lt;/li&gt;
